"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The roc_curve function from scikit-learn's metrics module expects the second argument to be the predicted probabilities of the positive class for each sample, but in this case, y_score is a 2D array where each row represents the predicted probabilities of all classes for a sample. Also, the first argument should be the true binary labels for each sample, but y_test is not binary. We should use the one-hot encoded version of y_test (y_onehot_test) instead.\",\n  \"patch\": \"28c28\\n<for i in range(n_classes):\\n---\\n>for i in range(n_classes):\\n29c29\\n<fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_test, y_score, pos_label=i)\\n---\\n>fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_onehot_test[:, i], y_score[:, i])\\n\"\n}"